HappyShop - project - client/customer - category

purpose:
    manages the customer - facing client application, providing the main shopping interface following MCV pattern  with customer UI styling

CustomerClient:
    Purpose:
    Provides the graphical user interface for new user registration, allowing
    users to create new accounts in the system.

    UI Components:
    - Username text field
    - Email text field
    - Password text field (with masked input)
    - Confirm Password text field
    - First Name text field
    - Last Name text field
    - "Create Account" / "Register" button
    - "Back to Login" button/link
    - Terms and Conditions checkbox
    - Error/validation message labels
    - Success message display

    Responsibilities:
    - Displays registration form to user
    - Captures new user information
    - Performs client-side validation (password match, email format, etc.)
    - Sends registration data to controller
    - Displays validation errors inline
    - Shows success message after registration
    - Provides password strength indicator
    - Implements UI styling and layout
    - Handles form submission

    Key Methods:
    - displayRegistrationForm(): Renders the registration interface
    - getUsername(): Retrieves entered username
    - getEmail(): Retrieves entered email
    - getPassword(): Retrieves entered password
    - getConfirmPassword(): Retrieves password confirmation
    - showError(field, message): Displays field-specific error
    - clearErrors(): Removes all error messages
    - validateEmail(email): Checks email format
    - validatePasswordMatch(): Checks if passwords match
    - showSuccess(message): Displays registration success
    - clearFields(): Clears all input fields
    - navigateToLogin(): Returns to login screen

    Usage:
    Created when user clicks "Sign Up" from LoginView. May have its own
    controller (RegisterController) or share LoginController. Validates input
    before sending to server. Shows success message and redirects to LoginView
    after successful registration. Provides user-friendly error messages for
    validation failures.

CustomerController:
    Purpose:
    Central controller that manages business logic and coordinates interactions
    between CustomerView, CustomerModel, and other components in the customer
    application.

    Responsibilities:
    - Handles user actions from CustomerView
    - Processes shopping cart operations (add, remove, update items)
    - Manages product browsing and search requests
    - Coordinates order placement process
    - Handles checkout workflow
    - Updates view based on model changes
    - Validates user input before processing
    - Manages error handling and user feedback
    - Coordinates with server for data operations

    Key Methods:
    - handleAddToCart(productId, quantity): Adds product to cart
    - handleRemoveFromCart(productId): Removes product from cart
    - handleUpdateQuantity(productId, newQuantity): Updates cart item quantity
    - handleProductSearch(keyword): Searches for products
    - handleCategoryFilter(category): Filters by category
    - handleCheckout(): Initiates checkout process
    - handlePlaceOrder(): Finalizes order placement
    - handleViewOrderHistory(): Retrieves customer's past orders
    - handleViewProductDetails(productId): Shows product information
    - updateCartDisplay(): Refreshes cart view
    - calculateCartTotal(): Computes total cart value
    - validateCheckout(): Ensures cart and shipping info are valid

    Usage:
    Created by CustomerClient during initialization. Receives all user interactions
    from CustomerView. Calls CustomerModel for data operations. Updates CustomerView
    based on results. Acts as the central coordinator for all customer operations.

CustomerModel:
    Purpose:
    Manages customer data, shopping cart state, and communicates with the server
    to retrieve products, process orders, and maintain customer information.

    Responsibilities:
    - Stores current shopping cart items
    - Maintains customer profile information
    - Communicates with server APIs (catalog, orders, payment)
    - Retrieves product information from server
    - Processes order submissions
    - Manages customer session data
    - Handles data persistence and caching
    - Validates business rules before operations
    - Manages inventory availability checks

    Key Methods:
    - getProducts(): Retrieves product list from server
    - getProductById(productId): Gets specific product details
    - searchProducts(keyword): Searches product catalog
    - getCart(): Returns current shopping cart
    - addToCart(product, quantity): Adds item to cart
    - removeFromCart(productId): Removes item from cart
    - updateCartQuantity(productId, quantity): Updates item quantity
    - clearCart(): Empties shopping cart
    - getCartTotal(): Calculates total cart value
    - getCartItemCount(): Returns number of items in cart
    - submitOrder(orderDetails): Sends order to server
    - getOrderHistory(): Retrieves customer's past orders
    - getCustomerProfile(): Returns customer information
    - updateProfile(profileData): Updates customer details
    - checkStockAvailability(productId, quantity): Verifies stock

    Usage:
    Called by CustomerController to perform data operations. Communicates with
    server-side APIs. Maintains shopping cart state throughout session. Provides
    data to controller which then updates the view. Handles all business logic
    related to customer operations.

CustomerUIStyle:
    Purpose:
    Defines the visual styling, themes, colors, and layout constants for the
    customer interface to ensure consistent UI design throughout the application.

    Style Properties:
    - Color scheme: Primary, secondary, accent colors
    - Font families: Headings, body text, buttons
    - Font sizes: Large (headings), medium (body), small (captions)
    - Button styles: Primary, secondary, danger (remove from cart)
    - Spacing constants: Margins, padding, gaps
    - Border styles: Radius, width, colors
    - Icon sizes and styles
    - Background colors and gradients
    - Hover and active states
    - Responsive breakpoints (if applicable)

    Responsibilities:
    - Provides consistent color palette across all views
    - Defines standard component styles (buttons, inputs, cards)
    - Ensures visual consistency and branding
    - Makes UI customization centralized and maintainable
    - Supports theme switching (light/dark mode) if implemented
    - Defines layout grid and spacing system
    - Provides accessibility-compliant color contrast

    Key Constants/Methods:
    - PRIMARY_COLOR: Main brand color
    - SECONDARY_COLOR: Supporting color
    - ACCENT_COLOR: Highlight color
    - BACKGROUND_COLOR: Main background
    - TEXT_COLOR: Default text color
    - ERROR_COLOR: Error messages (usually red)
    - SUCCESS_COLOR: Success messages (usually green)
    - BUTTON_STYLE: Standard button appearance
    - HEADING_FONT: Font for headings
    - BODY_FONT: Font for regular text
    - SPACING_SMALL, SPACING_MEDIUM, SPACING_LARGE: Standard spacing units
    - BORDER_RADIUS: Rounded corner radius
    - applyButtonStyle(button): Applies standard button styling
    - applyCardStyle(panel): Applies card/panel styling
    - applyInputStyle(textField): Applies input field styling

    Usage:
    Used by CustomerView to style all UI components consistently. Applied when
    creating buttons, panels, labels, and other UI elements. Ensures the entire
    customer application has a cohesive look and feel. Makes global style changes
    easy by updating values in one place.

CustomerView:
    Purpose:
    Provides the graphical user interface for the customer application, displaying
    products, shopping cart, orders, and all customer-facing screens.

    Main UI Sections:
    - Header: Logo, search bar, cart icon with item count, user menu
    - Navigation: Category menu, home, orders, profile links
    - Product Catalog: Grid/list of products with images and prices
    - Product Detail: Detailed view of selected product
    - Shopping Cart: List of items in cart with quantities and totals
    - Checkout: Shipping and payment information forms
    - Order History: List of past orders with status
    - Footer: Links, contact info, copyright

    UI Components:
    - Product cards with image, name, price, "Add to Cart" button
    - Search bar with auto-suggestions
    - Category filter dropdown/menu
    - Shopping cart panel with item list and total
    - Quantity selectors (+ and - buttons)
    - "Remove" buttons for cart items
    - Checkout form fields
    - Order summary display
    - Loading indicators
    - Error/success message notifications

    Responsibilities:
    - Renders all customer UI screens
    - Displays product catalog with filters
    - Shows shopping cart with current items
    - Provides checkout interface
    - Displays order history and details
    - Captures user input and actions
    - Sends events to CustomerController
    - Updates display based on controller commands
    - Applies CustomerUIStyle to all components
    - Provides smooth navigation between screens
    - Shows loading states during operations
    - Displays error and success messages

    Key Methods:
    - displayProductCatalog(products): Shows product grid
    - displayProductDetails(product): Shows detailed product view
    - displayShoppingCart(cart): Renders cart items
    - displayCheckoutForm(): Shows checkout screen
    - displayOrderHistory(orders): Shows past orders
    - updateCartIcon(itemCount): Updates cart badge with count
    - showProductAddedMessage(): Confirms item added to cart
    - showError(message): Displays error notification
    - showSuccess(message): Displays success notification
    - showLoading(): Shows loading indicator
    - hideLoading(): Hides loading indicator
    - refreshCartDisplay(): Updates cart view
    - highlightProduct(productId): Highlights a product (e.g., in search)
    - clearSearchResults(): Clears search display
    - enableCheckoutButton(enabled): Enables/disables checkout
    - updateTotalDisplay(total): Updates cart total amount

    Usage:
    Created by CustomerClient during initialization. Controlled by CustomerController.
    Displays all customer-facing screens and captures user interactions. Sends
    events (button clicks, searches) to controller. Updated by controller based on
    model changes. Applies CustomerUIStyle for consistent appearance. User's main
    interface for shopping experience.
